==English==

===Etymology===
From [[localize]] + [[-ation]]; compare French ''[[localisation#French|localisation]]''

===Alternative spellings===
* [[localisation]] (''British'')

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[act]] of [[localize|localizing]].
# The [[state]] of being localized.
# {{context|software engineering}} The act or [[process]] of making a [[product]] [[suitable]] for use in a particular [[country]] or [[region]], typically by [[translate|translating]] text into the [[language]] of that country or region and, if necessary, ensuring [[support]] of other [[character set]]s.

